# Overview

1. The code should be small and reusable.  
2. we must use lombok at every place in order to avoid boilerplate codes.  
3. We have to use mapper from mapstruct whenever we do any transformation from one object to another.
4. We must use querydsl to write our database logic.
5. Place methods or funtion in correct class, like using Utils or constants to improve reusability. 
6. dont over do code implementation, just perform a happy path and we iterate slowly from there. dont do too many things.

